    <note type="dates"><date>1843–1907</date></note>
    
    <note type="biography">
        <p>Politician. Called to the bar, 1870, and worked as a special pleader. Liberal MP for Brecon, 1880–5; for South Bedfordshire (Luton), 1885, 1886, 1892. Supported working-class housing and education in Battersea, London. Made Baron Battersea, 1892.</p></note>
